    "byte_equivalent_means": "REC1_T1 verbatim text shall appear in each future phase's sealed JSON body in a field that is included in the canonical seal computation. Cross-references to e2ae683 (seal 769eac99...), b3b93f3 (P1 supplement, seal a99898a4...), 508285f (P2 supplement, seal 84cecb78...), b015a35 (P3 supplement, seal 8d8abdbe...), and 2869945 (L1 memo, seal e41690d6...) shall be present in the same body. Any future phase that fails to carry REC1_T1 byte-equivalent without explicit operator override is a chain-integrity defect and shall trigger a carry-forward supplement of its own (analogous to b3b93f3 for P1, 508285f for P2, b015a35 for P3, this supplement for P4) before the next phase is authored. P6 is the load-bearing execution phase where REC1_T1 chain-of-custody matters most: P6 produces the actual closed_trades count that REC1_T1's 25/y tripwire is evaluated against."
  },
  "recommended_future_p6_authorization_language": {
